com.mapbox.services.android.navigation.v5.navigation

Class RouteRefresh

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.mapbox.services.android.navigation.v5.navigation.RouteRefresh

  • public final class RouteRefresh
extends Object
    This class allows the developer to interact with the Directions Refresh API, receiving updated annotations for a route previously requested with the enableRefresh flag.

    • Method Detail

      • refresh

        @Deprecated
public void refresh(RouteProgress routeProgress)
        Deprecated. use refresh(RouteProgress, RefreshCallback) instead
        Refreshes the DirectionsRoute included in the RouteProgress and returns it to the callback that was originally passed in. The client will then have to update their DirectionsRoute with the LegAnnotations returned in this response. The leg annotations start at the current leg index of the RouteProgress

        Note that if RefreshCallback is not passed in RouteRefresh(String, RefreshCallback) this call will be ignored.

        Parameters:
        routeProgress - to refresh via the route and current leg index

      • refresh

        public void refresh(RouteProgress routeProgress,
                    RefreshCallback refreshCallback)
        Refreshes the DirectionsRoute included in the RouteProgress and returns it to the callback that was originally passed in. The client will then have to update their DirectionsRoute with the LegAnnotations returned in this response. The leg annotations start at the current leg index of the RouteProgress
        Parameters:
        routeProgress - to refresh via the route and current leg index
        refreshCallback - to call with updated routes
